  12,97,"12:94"
  12,98,"12:94"
  12,99,"Here the ‘couch’ does not mean a royal throne but the seat where Joseph used to sit and discharge the duties of his post; here prostration (sajdah) does not mean lying face down in the usual sense but bowing down and kneeling (ruku‘). This form of obeisance to a great man was prevalent in ancient times."
  12,100,"12:99"
  12,103,"12:102"